\begin{align*}
| \mathbf{b} |^2
&= \frac{\|\mathbf{c}\|^2 + \|\mathbf{a}\|^2}{2}
\\\\
&= \frac{6^2 + 9^2}{2}
\\\\
&= 81
\end{align*}

Thus, $\|\mathbf{b}\| = 9$. We can use the angle bisector relationship to find $\mathbf{b}$, which is given by the equation

\begin{align*}
\frac{\mathbf{a}}{\|\mathbf{a}\|} + \frac{\mathbf{c}}{\|\mathbf{c}\|}
&= \frac{\mathbf{b}}{\|\mathbf{b}\|}
\\\\
\frac{\mathbf{a}}{9} + \frac{\mathbf{c}}{6}
&= \frac{\mathbf{b}}{9}
\\\\
\mathbf{b}
&= 2\mathbf{a} + 3\mathbf{c}
\\\\
&= 2\begin{pmatrix} 7 \\ -4 \\ -4 \end{pmatrix} + 3\begin{pmatrix} -2 \\ -1 \\ 2 \end{pmatrix}
\\\\
&= \begin{pmatrix} 8 \\ -11 \\ 2 \end{pmatrix}
\end{align*}

So the vector $\mathbf{b}$ is $\boxed{\begin{pmatrix} 8 \\ -11 \\ 2 \end{pmatrix}}$.[/think] <answer> $\begin{pmatrix} 8 \\ -11 \\ 2 \end{pmatrix}$ </answer>

